{"id":14881821,"mediaExerciseId":"fe8c21e3-fe12-47c2-b426-72a91e007a70","exerciseName":"5","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":612487,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":786,"solutions":[{"id":6004736,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will look at how the price of a commodity can affect the price of similar commodities that are used in the same type of market. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Natural gas and oil are related goods which means that they practically follow the same trends since natural gas is a product of oil. Since they use natural oil, they can be affected by the fluctuation of its price. If the price of natural gas increases, their production will be affected. At the same time, if the price of oil goes down, the price of natural gas will go up which also affects them negatively.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":216,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/b33047c418599a0e52dae0da67d99a36/8971f4e789fb327cd0505b9f0c624471/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/b33047c418599a0e52dae0da67d99a36/8971f4e789fb327cd0505b9f0c624471/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"ced184a3-f623-4c3f-b7cc-4538bbdc906e","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":2}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320